WEBVTT

﻿1
00:01:58.994 --> 00:02:01.245
Easy. boy.

2
00:03:14.236 --> 00:03:16.279
What do you expect?
They're savages.

3
00:03:16.405 --> 00:03:18.781
One lot steals a goat from another lot.

4
00:03:18.907 --> 00:03:21.242
before you know it
they're ripping each other to pieces.

5
00:03:21.368 --> 00:03:23.828
I've never seen wildlings
do a thing like this.

6
00:03:23.954 --> 00:03:26.122
I never seen a thing like this.
not ever in my life.

7
00:03:26.248 --> 00:03:28.416
How close did you get?

8
00:03:28.542 --> 00:03:31.961
- Close as any man would.
- We should head back to the Wall.

9
00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:36.048
Do the dead frighten you?

10
00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:38.301
Our orders were to track the wildlings.

11
00:03:38.427 --> 00:03:41.637
We tracked them.
They won't trouble us no more.

12
00:03:41.763 --> 00:03:44.181
You don't think he'll ask us how they died?

13
00:03:46.435 --> 00:03:48.227
Get back on your horse.

14
00:03:52.941 --> 00:03:55.443
Whatever did it to them
could do it to us.

15
00:03:55.569 --> 00:03:57.153
They even killed the children.

16
00:03:58.113 --> 00:04:00.114
It's a good thing we're not children.

17
00:04:01.491 --> 00:04:04.285
You want to run away south.
run away.

18
00:04:04.411 --> 00:04:07.330
Of course.
they will behead you as a deserter.

19
00:04:07.456 --> 00:04:09.582
If I don't catch you first.

20
00:04:11.960 --> 00:04:14.253
Get back on your horse.

21
00:04:14.379 --> 00:04:16.714
I won't say it again.

22
00:04:47.829 --> 00:04:50.331
Your dead men seem
to have moved camp.

23
00:04:51.041 --> 00:04:52.708
They were here.

24
00:04:56.088 --> 00:04:57.755
See where they went.

25
00:05:44.261 --> 00:05:46.137
What is it?

26
00:05:47.431 --> 00:05:48.556
It's...

27
00:09:51.633 --> 00:09:54.093
Go on. Father's watching.

28
00:09:56.304 --> 00:09:58.013
And your mother.

29
00:10:04.187 --> 00:10:07.523
Fine work. as always.
Well done.

30
00:10:07.649 --> 00:10:09.316
Thank you.

31
00:10:09.442 --> 00:10:13.279
I love the detail that you've managed
to get in these corners.

32
00:10:13.405 --> 00:10:15.197
Quite beautiful.

33
00:10:15.323 --> 00:10:17.199
The stitching...

34
00:10:17.325 --> 00:10:19.535
No. no. no. This stitch is very...

35
00:10:21.246 --> 00:10:23.205
- It's beautiful.
- Thank you.

36
00:10:38.388 --> 00:10:41.140
And which one of you
was a marksman at ten?

37
00:10:42.183 --> 00:10:43.684
Keep practicing. Bran.

38
00:10:45.854 --> 00:10:47.813
Go on.

39
00:10:47.939 --> 00:10:50.607
Don't think too much. Bran.

40
00:10:53.028 --> 00:10:54.194
Relax your bow arm.

41
00:11:07.334 --> 00:11:08.834
- Quick. Bran!
- Faster.

42
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:12.421
Lord Stark!

43
00:11:14.466 --> 00:11:15.507
My lady.

44
00:11:16.551 --> 00:11:18.761
A guardsman just rode in from the hills.

45
00:11:18.887 --> 00:11:21.889
They've captured a deserter
from the Night's Watch.

46
00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:27.311
Get the lads to saddle their horses.

47
00:11:27.437 --> 00:11:29.396
Do you have to?

48
00:11:29.522 --> 00:11:31.607
He swore an oath. Cat.

49
00:11:31.733 --> 00:11:33.734
Law is law. my lady.

50
00:11:34.736 --> 00:11:36.820
Tell Bran he's coming too.

51
00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:40.324
Ned.

52
00:11:40.450 --> 00:11:42.743
Ten is too young
to see such things.

53
00:11:42.869 --> 00:11:44.411
He won't be a boy forever.

54
00:11:46.414 --> 00:11:48.082
And winter is coming.

55
00:12:07.227 --> 00:12:09.436
Good lad. go run back and get the rest.

56
00:12:15.568 --> 00:12:17.152
White walkers.

57
00:12:17.278 --> 00:12:19.988
I saw the white walkers.

58
00:12:20.115 --> 00:12:21.990
White walkers.

59
00:12:22.117 --> 00:12:25.160
The white walkers. I saw them.

60
00:12:33.962 --> 00:12:35.587
I know I broke my oath.

61
00:12:36.798 --> 00:12:38.298
And I know I'm a deserter.

62
00:12:39.175 --> 00:12:41.844
I should have gone back to the Wall
and warned them. but...

63
00:12:43.012 --> 00:12:45.013
I saw what I saw.

64
00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:46.682
I saw the white walkers.

65
00:12:48.643 --> 00:12:50.477
People need to know.

66
00:12:52.647 --> 00:12:54.481
If you can get word to my family...

67
00:12:54.607 --> 00:12:56.900
tell them I'm no coward.

68
00:12:57.026 --> 00:12:58.986
Tell them I'm sorry.

69
00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:17.671
Forgive me. Lord.

70
00:13:22.051 --> 00:13:24.219
In the name of Robert
of the House Baratheon.

71
00:13:24.345 --> 00:13:26.305
- the first of his name...
- Don't look away.

72
00:13:26.431 --> 00:13:29.266
...King of the Andals and the First Men...
- Father will know if you do.

73
00:13:29.392 --> 00:13:32.728
...Lord of the Seven Kingdoms
and protector of the realm.

74
00:13:32.854 --> 00:13:35.731
I. Eddard of the House Stark.

75
00:13:35.857 --> 00:13:38.400
Lord of Winterfell
and Warden of the North.

76
00:13:38.526 --> 00:13:40.986
sentence you to die.

77
00:13:55.793 --> 00:13:57.461
You did well.

78
00:14:25.657 --> 00:14:27.115
You understand why I did it?

79
00:14:27.242 --> 00:14:29.117
Jon said he was a deserter.

80
00:14:29.244 --> 00:14:31.787
But do you understand
why I had to kill him?

81
00:14:31.913 --> 00:14:33.539
"Our way is the old way"?

82
00:14:35.166 --> 00:14:38.835
The man who passes the sentence
should swing the sword.

83
00:14:39.879 --> 00:14:42.256
Is it true he saw the white walkers?

84
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:47.261
The white walkers have been gone
for thousands of years.

85
00:14:48.429 --> 00:14:49.930
So he was lying?

86
00:14:54.435 --> 00:14:56.770
A madman sees what he sees.

87
00:15:22.714 --> 00:15:24.631
What is it?

88
00:15:27.010 --> 00:15:28.677
Mountain lion?

89
00:15:30.054 --> 00:15:32.389
There are no mountain lions
in these woods.

90
00:16:18.561 --> 00:16:20.354
It's a freak.

91
00:16:21.731 --> 00:16:23.023
It's a direwolf.

92
00:16:32.283 --> 00:16:34.534
Tough old beast.

93
00:16:36.829 --> 00:16:38.914
There are no direwolves
south of the Wall.

94
00:16:39.791 --> 00:16:41.083
Now there are five.

95
00:16:42.710 --> 00:16:44.378
You want to hold it?

96
00:16:48.925 --> 00:16:50.425
Where will they go?

97
00:16:50.551 --> 00:16:52.260
Their mother's dead.

98
00:16:52.387 --> 00:16:53.929
They don't belong down here.

99
00:16:54.055 --> 00:16:57.849
Better a quick death.
They won't last without their mother.

100
00:16:57.975 --> 00:16:59.976
- Right. Give it here.
- No!

101
00:17:00.103 --> 00:17:01.770
Put away your blade.

102
00:17:01.896 --> 00:17:04.815
- I take orders from your father. not you.
- Please. Father!

103
00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:06.733
I'm sorry. Bran.

104
00:17:06.859 --> 00:17:07.901
Lord Stark?

105
00:17:09.696 --> 00:17:11.196
There are five pups.

106
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:14.658
One for each of the Stark children.

107
00:17:14.784 --> 00:17:17.285
The direwolf is the sigil of your house.

108
00:17:18.663 --> 00:17:20.872
They were meant to have them.

109
00:17:26.129 --> 00:17:28.296
You will train them yourselves.

110
00:17:28.423 --> 00:17:30.298
You will feed them yourselves.

111
00:17:30.425 --> 00:17:33.301
And if they die. you will
bury them yourselves.

112
00:17:41.936 --> 00:17:43.645
What about you?

113
00:17:44.522 --> 00:17:46.189
I'm not a Stark.

114
00:17:46.315 --> 00:17:48.400
Get on.

115
00:17:58.453 --> 00:17:59.911
What is it?

116
00:18:04.125 --> 00:18:07.627
The runt of the litter.
That one's yours. Snow.

117
00:19:07.814 --> 00:19:10.982
As your brother.
I feel it's my duty to warn you...

118
00:19:12.235 --> 00:19:14.236
you worry too much.

119
00:19:14.362 --> 00:19:17.697
- It's starting to show.
- And you never worry about anything.

120
00:19:18.991 --> 00:19:22.911
When we were seven and you jumped off
the cliffs at Casterly Rock.

121
00:19:23.037 --> 00:19:27.415
100-foot drop into the water...
you were never afraid.

122
00:19:27.542 --> 00:19:30.168
There was nothing to be afraid of
until you told Father.

123
00:19:30.294 --> 00:19:33.880
"We're Lannisters.
Lannisters don't act like fools."

124
00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:39.845
- What if Jon Arryn told someone?
- But who would he tell?

125
00:19:41.222 --> 00:19:42.347
My husband.

126
00:19:42.473 --> 00:19:46.226
If he told the king. both our heads would
be skewered on the city gates by now.

127
00:19:47.770 --> 00:19:50.897
Whatever Jon Arryn knew or didn't know.
it died with him.

128
00:19:51.774 --> 00:19:53.608
And Robert will choose
a new Hand of the King.

129
00:19:53.734 --> 00:19:57.320
someone to do his job while he's off
fucking boars and hunting whores.

130
00:19:57.446 --> 00:19:59.114
Or is it the other way around?

131
00:20:00.658 --> 00:20:02.993
And life will go on.

132
00:20:03.119 --> 00:20:05.704
You should be the Hand of the King.

133
00:20:06.581 --> 00:20:08.415
That's an honor I can do without.

134
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:10.166
Their days are too long.

135
00:20:10.293 --> 00:20:11.960
their lives are too short.

136
00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:52.709
All these years.

137
00:20:52.835 --> 00:20:55.962
and I still feel like an outsider
when I come here.

138
00:20:57.798 --> 00:20:59.466
You have five northern children.

139
00:21:00.718 --> 00:21:03.011
You're not an outsider.

140
00:21:03.137 --> 00:21:05.639
I wonder if the old gods agree.

141
00:21:06.891 --> 00:21:08.767
It's your gods with all the rules.

142
00:21:15.524 --> 00:21:17.859
I am so sorry. my love.

143
00:21:18.986 --> 00:21:22.614
- Tell me.
- There was a raven from King's Landing.

144
00:21:24.742 --> 00:21:26.284
Jon Arryn is dead.

145
00:21:26.410 --> 00:21:28.912
A fever took him.

146
00:21:31.832 --> 00:21:33.959
I know he was like a father to you.

147
00:21:37.088 --> 00:21:40.131
- Your sister. the boy?
- They both have their health.

148
00:21:40.257 --> 00:21:42.258
gods be good.

149
00:21:52.520 --> 00:21:53.853
The raven brought more news.

150
00:21:55.982 --> 00:21:58.358
The king rides for Winterfell...

151
00:21:59.402 --> 00:22:02.195
with the queen and all the rest of them.

152
00:22:03.114 --> 00:22:05.448
If he's coming this far north...

153
00:22:07.118 --> 00:22:09.035
there's only one thing he's after.

154
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:12.539
You can always say no. Ned.

155
00:22:20.881 --> 00:22:24.592
We'll need plenty of candles
for Lord Tyrion's chamber.

156
00:22:24.719 --> 00:22:28.471
- I'm told he reads all night.
- I'm told he drinks all night.

157
00:22:28.597 --> 00:22:31.766
How much could he possibly drink?
A man of his...

158
00:22:31.892 --> 00:22:33.435
stature?

159
00:22:33.561 --> 00:22:36.438
We've brought up eight barrels of ale
from the cellar.

160
00:22:36.564 --> 00:22:37.772
Perhaps we'll find out.

161
00:22:37.898 --> 00:22:39.733
In any case. candles.

162
00:22:45.865 --> 00:22:48.783
Why is your mother so dead set on us
getting pretty for the king?

163
00:22:48.909 --> 00:22:51.661
It's for the queen. I bet.
I hear she's a sleek bit of mink.

164
00:22:51.787 --> 00:22:53.830
I hear the prince is a right royal prick.

165
00:22:53.956 --> 00:22:57.417
Think of all those southern girls he
gets to stab with his right royal prick.

166
00:22:59.336 --> 00:23:01.463
Go on. Tommy. shear him good.

167
00:23:01.589 --> 00:23:03.882
He's never met a girl he likes better
than his own hair.

168
00:23:40.878 --> 00:23:43.546
Gods. but they grow fast.

169
00:23:46.008 --> 00:23:47.509
Brandon!

170
00:23:47.635 --> 00:23:50.637
I saw the king.
He's got hundreds of people.

171
00:23:50.763 --> 00:23:53.848
How many times have I told you?
No climbing.

172
00:23:53.974 --> 00:23:56.935
But he's coming right now. down our road.

173
00:24:03.943 --> 00:24:06.361
I want you to promise me.

174
00:24:06.487 --> 00:24:08.154
no more climbing.

175
00:24:12.993 --> 00:24:14.160
I promise.

176
00:24:16.330 --> 00:24:19.374
- Do you know what?
- What?

177
00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:21.709
You always look at your feet
before you lie.

178
00:24:23.879 --> 00:24:25.630
Run and find your father.

179
00:24:25.756 --> 00:24:27.799
Tell him the king is close.

180
00:25:12.219 --> 00:25:15.597
Where's Arya?
Sansa. where's your sister?

181
00:25:25.900 --> 00:25:28.067
Hey. hey. hey. hey.

182
00:25:28.194 --> 00:25:30.111
What are you doing with that on?

183
00:25:32.531 --> 00:25:34.616
Go on.

184
00:25:35.993 --> 00:25:37.660
Move!

185
00:26:59.827 --> 00:27:01.661
Your Grace.

186
00:27:06.166 --> 00:27:07.834
You've got fat.

187
00:27:19.930 --> 00:27:21.472
- Cat!
- Your Grace.

188
00:27:25.602 --> 00:27:29.063
Nine years... Why haven't I seen you?
Where the hell have you been?

189
00:27:29.189 --> 00:27:32.734
Guarding the North for you. Your Grace.
Winterfell is yours.

190
00:27:36.655 --> 00:27:39.198
- Where's the Imp?
- Will you shut up?

191
00:27:39.325 --> 00:27:40.825
Who have we here?

192
00:27:42.202 --> 00:27:43.536
You must be Robb.

193
00:27:46.498 --> 00:27:48.624
My. you're a pretty one.

194
00:27:50.044 --> 00:27:51.919
Your name is?

195
00:27:52.046 --> 00:27:53.421
Arya.

196
00:27:54.631 --> 00:27:57.216
Show us your muscles.

197
00:27:58.552 --> 00:28:00.845
You'll be a soldier.

198
00:28:03.724 --> 00:28:06.142
That's Jaime Lannister.
the queen's twin brother.

199
00:28:06.268 --> 00:28:08.394
Would you please shut up?

200
00:28:17.946 --> 00:28:21.824
My queen.

201
00:28:21.950 --> 00:28:23.951
Take me to your crypt.
I want to pay my respects.

202
00:28:24.078 --> 00:28:25.912
We've been riding for a month. my love.

203
00:28:26.413 --> 00:28:28.039
Surely the dead can wait.

204
00:28:28.165 --> 00:28:30.041
Ned.

205
00:28:39.718 --> 00:28:40.927
Where's the Imp?

206
00:28:44.431 --> 00:28:46.432
Where is our brother?

207
00:28:46.558 --> 00:28:48.309
Go and find the little beast.

208
00:28:50.687 --> 00:28:52.355
Tell me about Jon Arryn.

209
00:28:53.607 --> 00:28:55.817
One minute he was fine and then...

210
00:28:57.027 --> 00:28:59.779
burned right through him.
whatever it was.

211
00:29:00.948 --> 00:29:02.949
I loved that man.

212
00:29:03.075 --> 00:29:04.409
We both did.

213
00:29:04.535 --> 00:29:08.871
He never had to teach you much.
but me? You remember me at 16?

214
00:29:08.997 --> 00:29:10.832
All I wanted to do

215
00:29:10.958 --> 00:29:13.584
was crack skulls and fuck girls.

216
00:29:13.710 --> 00:29:16.838
- He showed me what was what.
- Aye.

217
00:29:16.964 --> 00:29:19.590
Don't look at me like that.
It's not his fault I didn't listen.

218
00:29:24.138 --> 00:29:26.180
I need you. Ned.

219
00:29:26.306 --> 00:29:29.976
down at King's Landing. not up here
where you're no damn use to anybody.

220
00:29:31.854 --> 00:29:33.646
Lord Eddard Stark...

221
00:29:34.606 --> 00:29:37.066
I would name you the Hand of the King.

222
00:29:41.530 --> 00:29:43.656
I'm not worthy of the honor.

223
00:29:43.782 --> 00:29:45.199
I'm not trying to honor you.

224
00:29:45.325 --> 00:29:47.034
I'm trying to get you to run my kingdom

225
00:29:47.161 --> 00:29:50.872
while I eat. drink and whore my way
to an early grave.

226
00:29:50.998 --> 00:29:52.832
Damn it. Ned. stand up.

227
00:29:54.376 --> 00:29:56.335
You helped me win the Iron Throne.

228
00:29:56.462 --> 00:29:59.172
now help me keep the damn thing.

229
00:29:59.298 --> 00:30:01.674
We were meant to rule together.

230
00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:05.636
If your sister had lived.
we'd have been bound by blood.

231
00:30:06.597 --> 00:30:08.181
Well. it's not too late.

232
00:30:09.850 --> 00:30:11.517
I have a son.
you have a daughter.

233
00:30:13.353 --> 00:30:15.021
We'll join our houses.

234
00:30:40.214 --> 00:30:43.174
It is true what they say
about the northern girls.

235
00:30:51.391 --> 00:30:53.726
Did you hear the king's in Winterfell?

236
00:30:53.852 --> 00:30:55.478
I did hear something about that.

237
00:30:55.604 --> 00:30:57.772
And the queen and her twin brother.

238
00:30:57.898 --> 00:31:00.942
They say that he is the most handsome man
in the Seven Kingdoms.

239
00:31:01.068 --> 00:31:02.944
And the other brother?

240
00:31:03.070 --> 00:31:06.280
- The queen has two brothers?
- There's the pretty one...

241
00:31:07.491 --> 00:31:09.200
and there's the clever one.

242
00:31:12.120 --> 00:31:14.372
I hear they call him the Imp.

243
00:31:14.498 --> 00:31:16.290
I hear he hates that nickname.

244
00:31:16.416 --> 00:31:19.794
I hear he's more than earned it.

245
00:31:19.920 --> 00:31:22.171
I hear he's a drunken little lecher.

246
00:31:22.297 --> 00:31:24.757
prone to all manner of perversions.

247
00:31:24.883 --> 00:31:26.676
Clever girl.

248
00:31:28.428 --> 00:31:30.263
We've been expecting you. Lord Tyrion.

249
00:31:31.598 --> 00:31:33.182
Have you?

250
00:31:33.308 --> 00:31:34.684
Already?

251
00:31:37.604 --> 00:31:40.314
The gods gave me one blessing.

252
00:31:45.195 --> 00:31:47.697
- Don't get up.
- My lord.

253
00:31:47.823 --> 00:31:51.492
Should I explain to you the meaning of
a closed door in a whorehouse. brother?

254
00:31:51.618 --> 00:31:53.661
You have much to teach me. no doubt.

255
00:31:53.787 --> 00:31:56.956
but our sister craves your attention.

256
00:31:57.666 --> 00:31:59.667
She has odd cravings. our sister.

257
00:31:59.793 --> 00:32:01.836
A family trait.

258
00:32:01.962 --> 00:32:04.422
Now. the Starks are feasting us at sundown.

259
00:32:05.424 --> 00:32:09.385
- Don't leave me alone with these people.
- I'm sorry. I've begun the feast a bit early.

260
00:32:09.511 --> 00:32:12.847
And this is the first of many courses.

261
00:32:12.973 --> 00:32:15.182
I thought you might say that.

262
00:32:15.309 --> 00:32:17.935
But since we're short on time...

263
00:32:18.061 --> 00:32:19.353
Come on. girls.

264
00:32:25.319 --> 00:32:27.111
See you at sundown.

265
00:32:27.237 --> 00:32:29.322
Close the door!

266
00:32:41.752 --> 00:32:44.503
Did you have to bury her
in a place like this?

267
00:32:46.381 --> 00:32:48.591
She should be on a hill somewhere

268
00:32:48.717 --> 00:32:51.052
with the sun and the clouds above her.

269
00:32:51.178 --> 00:32:53.220
She was my sister.

270
00:32:53.347 --> 00:32:55.014
This is where she belongs.

271
00:32:56.183 --> 00:32:58.517
She belonged with me.

272
00:33:03.982 --> 00:33:07.193
In my dreams.
I kill him every night.

273
00:33:08.737 --> 00:33:13.032
It's done. Your Grace.
The Targaryens are gone.

274
00:33:16.244 --> 00:33:18.162
Not all of them.

275
00:33:29.091 --> 00:33:31.050
Daenerys!

276
00:33:34.221 --> 00:33:35.930
Daenerys.

277
00:33:36.056 --> 00:33:38.057
There's our bride-to-be.

278
00:33:39.059 --> 00:33:41.644
Look. a gift from Illyrio.

279
00:33:43.230 --> 00:33:44.814
Touch it.

280
00:33:44.940 --> 00:33:47.149
Go on. feel the fabric.

281
00:33:55.242 --> 00:33:57.076
Isn't he a gracious host?

282
00:34:00.455 --> 00:34:04.125
We've been his guests for over a year
and he's never asked us for anything.

283
00:34:04.251 --> 00:34:06.127
Illyrio's no fool.

284
00:34:06.253 --> 00:34:08.045
He knows I won't forget my friends

285
00:34:08.171 --> 00:34:10.423
when I come into my throne.

286
00:34:14.761 --> 00:34:16.512
You still slouch.

287
00:34:20.892 --> 00:34:23.185
Let them see.

288
00:34:25.981 --> 00:34:28.733
You have a woman's body now.

289
00:34:46.626 --> 00:34:48.627
I need you to be perfect today.

290
00:34:51.173 --> 00:34:52.548
Can you do that for me?

291
00:34:56.094 --> 00:34:58.679
You don't want to wake the dragon. do you?

292
00:35:00.640 --> 00:35:01.682
No.

293
00:35:08.815 --> 00:35:11.400
When they write the history
of my reign. sweet sister.

294
00:35:11.526 --> 00:35:13.486
they will say it began today.

295
00:35:37.219 --> 00:35:38.886
It's too hot. my lady.

296
00:36:00.158 --> 00:36:02.076
Where is he?

297
00:36:02.202 --> 00:36:05.079
The Dothraki are not known
for their punctuality.

298
00:36:22.556 --> 00:36:24.473
May I present my honored guests?

299
00:36:24.599 --> 00:36:28.143
Viserys of House Targaryen.

300
00:36:28.270 --> 00:36:29.770
the third of his name.

301
00:36:29.896 --> 00:36:33.274
the rightful King of the Andals
and the First Men.

302
00:36:33.400 --> 00:36:34.692
and his sister.

303
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:37.695
Daenerys of House Targaryen.

304
00:36:40.740 --> 00:36:43.158
Do you see how long his hair is?

305
00:36:43.285 --> 00:36:46.078
When Dothraki are defeated in combat

306
00:36:46.204 --> 00:36:49.790
they cut off their braid
so the whole world can see their shame.

307
00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:53.752
Khal Drogo has never been defeated.

308
00:36:55.213 --> 00:36:59.091
He's a savage. of course.
but he's one of the finest killers alive.

309
00:37:00.468 --> 00:37:02.595
And you will be his queen.

310
00:37:03.388 --> 00:37:05.264
Come forward. my dear.

311
00:37:45.388 --> 00:37:46.513
Where is he going?

312
00:37:46.640 --> 00:37:49.350
- The ceremony is over.
- But he... But he didn't say anything.

313
00:37:49.476 --> 00:37:50.601
Did he like her?

314
00:37:50.727 --> 00:37:54.480
Trust me. Your Grace.
if he didn't like her. we'd know.

315
00:37:57.609 --> 00:37:59.860
It won't be long now.

316
00:37:59.986 --> 00:38:03.614
Soon you will cross the narrow sea
and take back your father's throne.

317
00:38:04.866 --> 00:38:08.702
The people drink secret toasts
to your health.

318
00:38:08.828 --> 00:38:11.288
They cry out for their true king.

319
00:38:14.834 --> 00:38:16.710
When will they be married?

320
00:38:16.836 --> 00:38:20.381
Soon.
The Dothraki never stay still for long.

321
00:38:20.507 --> 00:38:22.758
Is it true they lie with their horses?

322
00:38:23.510 --> 00:38:25.803
I wouldn't ask Khal Drogo.

323
00:38:25.929 --> 00:38:28.055
Do you take me for a fool?

324
00:38:28.181 --> 00:38:29.890
I take you for a king.

325
00:38:30.016 --> 00:38:33.143
Kings lack the caution
of common men.

326
00:38:33.269 --> 00:38:34.979
My apologies if I've given offense.

327
00:38:35.105 --> 00:38:37.690
I know how to play a man like Drogo.

328
00:38:37.816 --> 00:38:40.609
I give him a queen
and he gives me an army.

329
00:38:41.528 --> 00:38:43.570
I don't want to be his queen.

330
00:38:48.660 --> 00:38:50.035
I want to go home.

331
00:38:50.704 --> 00:38:52.037
So do I.

332
00:38:53.206 --> 00:38:55.499
I want us both to go home.

333
00:38:55.625 --> 00:38:57.835
but they took it from us.

334
00:38:57.961 --> 00:38:59.753
So tell me. sweet sister.

335
00:38:59.879 --> 00:39:01.547
how do we go home?

336
00:39:04.259 --> 00:39:05.426
I don't know.

337
00:39:05.552 --> 00:39:07.803
We go home with an army.

338
00:39:09.889 --> 00:39:12.182
With Khal Drogo's army.

339
00:39:13.393 --> 00:39:16.395
I would let his whole tribe fuck you.

340
00:39:16.521 --> 00:39:19.606
all 40.000 men and their horses too.

341
00:39:19.733 --> 00:39:21.400
if that's what it took.

342
00:39:38.710 --> 00:39:41.211
Do you think Joffrey will like me?

343
00:39:41.337 --> 00:39:43.547
What if he thinks I'm ugly?

344
00:39:43.673 --> 00:39:47.092
Then he is the stupidest
prince that ever lived.

345
00:39:49.763 --> 00:39:51.096
He's so handsome.

346
00:39:52.265 --> 00:39:54.975
When would we be married?
Soon? Or do we have to wait?

347
00:39:55.101 --> 00:39:58.187
Hush now.
Your father hasn't even said yes.

348
00:39:58.313 --> 00:39:59.980
Why would he say no?

349
00:40:00.106 --> 00:40:03.025
He'd be the second most powerful man
in the kingdoms.

350
00:40:03.151 --> 00:40:05.194
He'd have to leave home.

351
00:40:06.488 --> 00:40:08.864
He'd have to leave me.

352
00:40:09.866 --> 00:40:11.992
And so would you.

353
00:40:12.118 --> 00:40:14.453
You left your home to come here.

354
00:40:14.579 --> 00:40:16.330
And I'd be queen someday.

355
00:40:18.291 --> 00:40:19.833
Please make Father say yes!

356
00:40:19.959 --> 00:40:21.752
- Sansa...
- Please. please!

357
00:40:21.878 --> 00:40:24.755
It's the only thing I ever wanted.

358
00:40:38.645 --> 00:40:40.813
Fill that up!
Boys. Rodrik. come on.

359
00:40:40.939 --> 00:40:42.981
Come on!

360
00:40:43.108 --> 00:40:45.859
Come here. you little beauty!

361
00:41:01.668 --> 00:41:02.960
Is he dead yet?

362
00:41:08.424 --> 00:41:09.508
Uncle Benjen.

363
00:41:12.512 --> 00:41:13.720
You got bigger.

364
00:41:15.098 --> 00:41:16.682
Rode all day.

365
00:41:16.808 --> 00:41:19.393
Didn't want to leave you alone
with the Lannisters.

366
00:41:19.519 --> 00:41:20.853
Why aren't you at the feast?

367
00:41:20.979 --> 00:41:23.730
Lady Stark thought it might
insult the royal family

368
00:41:23.857 --> 00:41:25.774
to seat a bastard in their midst.

369
00:41:26.609 --> 00:41:28.986
Well. you're always
welcome on the Wall.

370
00:41:29.112 --> 00:41:31.071
No bastard was ever
refused a seat there.

371
00:41:31.197 --> 00:41:32.906
So take me with you
when you go back.

372
00:41:33.032 --> 00:41:35.909
- Jon...
- Father will let me if you ask him.

373
00:41:36.035 --> 00:41:37.828
I know he will.

374
00:41:40.540 --> 00:41:42.624
The Wall isn't going anywhere.

375
00:41:42.750 --> 00:41:45.419
I'm ready to swear your oath.

376
00:41:45.545 --> 00:41:48.672
You don't understand
what you'd be giving up.

377
00:41:48.798 --> 00:41:50.716
We have no families.

378
00:41:50.842 --> 00:41:54.553
- None of us will ever father sons.
- I don't care about that.

379
00:41:54.679 --> 00:41:57.639
You might. if you knew what it meant.

380
00:42:01.019 --> 00:42:03.478
I'd better get inside.

381
00:42:03.605 --> 00:42:05.898
rescue your father from his guests.

382
00:42:08.943 --> 00:42:10.986
We'll talk later.

383
00:42:19.412 --> 00:42:21.747
Your uncle's in the Night's Watch.

384
00:42:24.709 --> 00:42:27.044
What are you doing back there?

385
00:42:27.170 --> 00:42:29.379
Preparing for a night with your family.

386
00:42:34.594 --> 00:42:36.511
I've always wanted to see the Wall.

387
00:42:36.638 --> 00:42:38.430
You're Tyrion Lannister.

388
00:42:38.556 --> 00:42:40.098
the queen's brother?

389
00:42:40.225 --> 00:42:41.892
My greatest accomplishment.

390
00:42:43.436 --> 00:42:46.104
And you. you're Ned Stark's bastard.
aren't you?

391
00:42:49.567 --> 00:42:51.735
Did I offend you? Sorry.

392
00:42:53.863 --> 00:42:56.323
You are the bastard. though.

393
00:42:57.617 --> 00:42:59.952
Lord Eddard Stark is my father.

394
00:43:01.204 --> 00:43:03.830
And Lady Stark is not your mother.

395
00:43:03.957 --> 00:43:06.959
making you... the bastard.

396
00:43:08.461 --> 00:43:11.088
Let me give you some advice. bastard.

397
00:43:12.257 --> 00:43:14.049
Never forget what you are.

398
00:43:14.175 --> 00:43:16.510
The rest of the world will not.

399
00:43:16.636 --> 00:43:18.220
Wear it like armor...

400
00:43:19.013 --> 00:43:21.306
and it can never be used to hurt you.

401
00:43:22.976 --> 00:43:25.644
What the hell do you know
about being a bastard?

402
00:43:28.106 --> 00:43:30.565
All dwarves are bastards
in their father's eyes.

403
00:43:52.255 --> 00:43:53.880
You at a feast...

404
00:43:54.841 --> 00:43:56.508
it's like a bear in a trap.

405
00:43:58.511 --> 00:44:00.095
The boy I beheaded...

406
00:44:01.431 --> 00:44:04.349
- did you know him?
- Of course I did. Just a lad.

407
00:44:05.518 --> 00:44:07.602
But he was tough. Ned.

408
00:44:07.729 --> 00:44:08.979
a true ranger.

409
00:44:10.732 --> 00:44:12.482
He was talking madness.

410
00:44:13.693 --> 00:44:15.444
Said the walkers slaughtered his friends.

411
00:44:15.570 --> 00:44:17.863
The two he was with are still missing.

412
00:44:19.532 --> 00:44:22.993
Hmph. A wildling ambush.

413
00:44:23.995 --> 00:44:25.078
Maybe.

414
00:44:26.372 --> 00:44:28.915
Direwolves south of the Wall.

415
00:44:29.042 --> 00:44:31.251
talk of the walkers.

416
00:44:31.377 --> 00:44:33.920
and my brother might be
the next Hand of the King.

417
00:44:35.131 --> 00:44:40.385
Winter is coming.

418
00:44:42.055 --> 00:44:44.890
- Uncle Benjen.
- Robb boy.

419
00:44:45.016 --> 00:44:46.475
- How are you?
- I'm good.

420
00:44:49.937 --> 00:44:52.689
Is this your first time
in the North. Your Grace?

421
00:44:52.815 --> 00:44:55.567
Yes. Lovely country.

422
00:44:59.364 --> 00:45:02.699
I'm sure it's very grim
after King's Landing.

423
00:45:03.993 --> 00:45:08.372
I remember how scared I was when
Ned brought me up here for the first time.

424
00:45:10.583 --> 00:45:12.167
Hello. little dove.

425
00:45:13.169 --> 00:45:15.337
But you are a beauty.

426
00:45:15.463 --> 00:45:17.756
- How old are you?
- Thirteen. Your Grace.

427
00:45:17.882 --> 00:45:20.467
You're tall. Still growing?

428
00:45:20.593 --> 00:45:22.427
I think so. Your Grace.

429
00:45:22.553 --> 00:45:24.679
And have you bled yet?

430
00:45:29.811 --> 00:45:31.269
No. Your Grace.

431
00:45:32.772 --> 00:45:34.398
Your dress. did you make it?

432
00:45:36.192 --> 00:45:39.444
Such talent.
You must make something for me.

433
00:45:41.364 --> 00:45:44.408
I hear we might share
a grandchild someday.

434
00:45:45.451 --> 00:45:46.618
I hear the same.

435
00:45:46.744 --> 00:45:48.954
Your daughter will do well in the capital.

436
00:45:49.080 --> 00:45:52.416
Such a beauty shouldn't stay
hidden up here forever.

437
00:46:09.434 --> 00:46:12.060
- Your pardon.
- I hear we might be neighbors soon.

438
00:46:12.186 --> 00:46:15.647
- I hope it's true.
- Yes. the king has honored me with his offer.

439
00:46:15.773 --> 00:46:18.984
I'm sure we'll have a tournament to
celebrate your new title. if you accept.

440
00:46:19.110 --> 00:46:21.194
It would be good
to have you on the field.

441
00:46:21.320 --> 00:46:23.697
The competition has become a bit stale.

442
00:46:23.823 --> 00:46:26.074
- I don't fight in tournaments.
- No?

443
00:46:26.200 --> 00:46:27.742
Getting a little old for it?

444
00:46:29.704 --> 00:46:31.746
I don't fight in tournaments

445
00:46:31.873 --> 00:46:34.249
because when I fight a man for real.

446
00:46:34.375 --> 00:46:36.126
I don't want him to know what I can do.

447
00:46:38.421 --> 00:46:39.796
Well said.

448
00:46:41.174 --> 00:46:42.507
Arya!

449
00:46:44.844 --> 00:46:46.553
It's not funny!

450
00:46:46.679 --> 00:46:49.306
She always does this.

451
00:46:49.432 --> 00:46:51.850
This was my favorite dress
and she ruined it.

452
00:46:51.976 --> 00:46:54.436
She always does it
and it's not funny!

453
00:46:54.562 --> 00:46:56.396
Time for bed.

454
00:47:07.492 --> 00:47:09.159
I'm a Northman.

455
00:47:10.870 --> 00:47:15.373
I belong here with you. not down south
in that rats' nest they call a capital.

456
00:47:16.417 --> 00:47:19.169
I won't let him take you.

457
00:47:20.713 --> 00:47:23.298
The king takes what he wants.

458
00:47:23.424 --> 00:47:25.717
That's why he's king.

459
00:47:26.761 --> 00:47:30.430
I'll say. "Listen. fat man."

460
00:47:31.724 --> 00:47:34.851
"You are not taking
my husband anywhere.

461
00:47:34.977 --> 00:47:36.895
"He belongs to me now."

462
00:47:40.650 --> 00:47:42.692
How did he get so fat?

463
00:47:42.818 --> 00:47:47.113
He only stops eating
when it's time for a drink.

464
00:47:48.741 --> 00:47:51.159
It's Maester Luwin. my lord.

465
00:47:52.620 --> 00:47:54.538
Send him in.

466
00:47:56.832 --> 00:47:59.167
Pardon. my lord. my lady.

467
00:47:59.293 --> 00:48:01.795
A rider in the night...

468
00:48:01.921 --> 00:48:04.089
from your sister.

469
00:48:11.806 --> 00:48:14.432
- Stay.
- This was sent from the Eyrie.

470
00:48:20.439 --> 00:48:22.691
What's she doing at the Eyrie?

471
00:48:22.817 --> 00:48:25.360
She hasn't been back there
since her wedding.

472
00:48:33.828 --> 00:48:35.704
What news?

473
00:48:37.331 --> 00:48:39.791
She's fled the capital.

474
00:48:42.128 --> 00:48:44.671
She says Jon Arryn was murdered.

475
00:48:44.797 --> 00:48:46.673
By the Lannisters.

476
00:48:46.799 --> 00:48:49.467
She says the king is in danger.

477
00:48:49.594 --> 00:48:51.845
She's fresh widowed. Cat.

478
00:48:51.971 --> 00:48:53.597
She doesn't know what she's saying.

479
00:48:53.723 --> 00:48:59.019
Lysa's head would be on a spike right now
if the wrong people had found that letter.

480
00:48:59.145 --> 00:49:01.313
Do you think she would risk her life.

481
00:49:01.439 --> 00:49:03.023
her son's life.

482
00:49:03.149 --> 00:49:06.526
if she wasn't certain
her husband was murdered?

483
00:49:13.743 --> 00:49:15.619
If this news is true...

484
00:49:15.745 --> 00:49:19.289
and the Lannisters conspire
against the throne.

485
00:49:19.415 --> 00:49:21.833
who but you can protect the king?

486
00:49:21.959 --> 00:49:24.210
They murdered the last Hand.

487
00:49:24.337 --> 00:49:26.546
Now you want Ned to take the job?

488
00:49:26.672 --> 00:49:30.550
The king rode for a month
to ask for Lord Stark's help.

489
00:49:30.676 --> 00:49:33.178
He's the only one he trusts.

490
00:49:34.680 --> 00:49:37.515
You swore the king an oath. my lord.

491
00:49:37.642 --> 00:49:41.227
He's spent half his life
fighting Robert's wars.

492
00:49:41.354 --> 00:49:43.355
He owes him nothing.

493
00:49:45.274 --> 00:49:48.485
Your father and brother
rode south once

494
00:49:48.611 --> 00:49:51.237
on a king's demand.

495
00:49:53.157 --> 00:49:55.283
A different time.

496
00:49:56.661 --> 00:49:58.745
A different king.

497
00:50:59.932 --> 00:51:03.435
When do I meet with the khal?
We need to begin planning the invasion.

498
00:51:03.561 --> 00:51:06.980
If Khal Drogo has promised you a crown.
you shall have it.

499
00:51:07.106 --> 00:51:10.150
- When?
- When their omens favor war.

500
00:51:11.277 --> 00:51:13.820
I piss on Dothraki omens.

501
00:51:13.946 --> 00:51:16.614
I've waited 17 years to get my throne back.

502
00:52:16.550 --> 00:52:21.513
A Dothraki wedding without at least
three deaths is considered a dull affair.

503
00:52:43.869 --> 00:52:46.913
A small gift. for the new khaleesi.

504
00:52:47.873 --> 00:52:50.458
Songs and histories from
the Seven Kingdoms.

505
00:52:52.127 --> 00:52:53.545
Thank you. ser.

506
00:52:55.256 --> 00:52:57.924
Are you from my country?

507
00:52:58.050 --> 00:53:00.093
Ser Jorah Mormont of Bear Island.

508
00:53:00.219 --> 00:53:02.929
I served your father for many years.

509
00:53:03.055 --> 00:53:06.015
Gods be good. I hope to
always serve the rightful king.

510
00:53:29.248 --> 00:53:31.916
Dragon's eggs. Daenerys.

511
00:53:32.042 --> 00:53:34.794
from the Shadow Lands beyond Asshai.

512
00:53:34.920 --> 00:53:37.839
The ages have turned them to stone.

513
00:53:37.965 --> 00:53:39.924
but they will always be beautiful.

514
00:53:42.177 --> 00:53:43.845
Thank you. Magister.

515
00:54:52.539 --> 00:54:54.582
She's beautiful.

516
00:54:58.837 --> 00:55:00.088
Ser Jorah. I...

517
00:55:00.214 --> 00:55:02.966
I don't know how to say "thank you"
in Dothraki.

518
00:55:03.092 --> 00:55:05.885
There is no word for "thank you"
in Dothraki.

519
00:55:27.074 --> 00:55:29.033
Make him happy.

520
00:56:28.427 --> 00:56:30.428
No.

521
00:56:33.766 --> 00:56:35.600
Do you know the common tongue?

522
00:56:40.439 --> 00:56:42.148
No.

523
00:56:46.403 --> 00:56:48.613
Is "no" the only word that you know?

524
00:56:50.115 --> 00:56:51.449
No.

525
00:57:19.812 --> 00:57:21.854
Rough night. Imp?

526
00:57:21.980 --> 00:57:23.940
If I get through this without squirting

527
00:57:24.066 --> 00:57:26.943
from one end or the other.
it'll be a miracle.

528
00:57:27.069 --> 00:57:28.861
I didn't pick you for a hunter.

529
00:57:28.987 --> 00:57:32.073
The greatest in the land -
my spear never misses.

530
00:57:33.158 --> 00:57:35.118
It's not hunting if you pay for it.

531
00:57:44.169 --> 00:57:46.212
Are you as good with a spear
as you used to be?

532
00:57:46.338 --> 00:57:48.798
No. but I'm still better than you.

533
00:57:51.802 --> 00:57:53.427
I know what I'm putting you through.

534
00:57:53.554 --> 00:57:55.221
Thank you for saying yes.

535
00:57:57.349 --> 00:57:59.642
I only ask you because I need you.

536
00:58:00.853 --> 00:58:03.396
You're a loyal friend. You hear me?

537
00:58:04.481 --> 00:58:06.065
A loyal friend.

538
00:58:06.191 --> 00:58:07.859
The last one I've got.

539
00:58:09.611 --> 00:58:11.779
- I hope I'll serve you well.
- You will.

540
00:58:13.073 --> 00:58:16.284
And I'll make sure you don't look
so fucking grim all the time.

541
00:58:17.619 --> 00:58:19.871
Come on. boys.
let's go kill some boar!

542
00:58:30.090 --> 00:58:31.591
Come on. you.

543
00:59:47.960 --> 00:59:50.753
Stop! Stop.

544
00:59:55.634 --> 00:59:57.885
Are you completely mad?

545
00:59:58.011 --> 01:00:00.513
- He saw us.
- It's all right. it's all right.

546
01:00:00.639 --> 01:00:02.682
- It's all right.
- He saw us!

547
01:00:02.808 --> 01:00:04.934
I heard you the first time.

548
01:00:09.690 --> 01:00:11.357
Quite the little climber. aren't you?

549
01:00:12.651 --> 01:00:15.444
- How old are you. boy?
- Ten.

550
01:00:15.570 --> 01:00:17.154
Ten.

551
01:00:25.998 --> 01:00:28.332
The things I do for love.

